{"author":{"id":"bf52274e4b8baa03d436abcc532c02b6a719b9a772a7e952e18fcc8627570e5f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774387345,"nonce":"2UPhfs0vvvxOxoV2jkhaWEeg58M=","title":"Invalid load crashes ccwl","message":"You sometimes have to load a ccwl workflow from another. And, we use `load` to do so. However, if the file being loaded does not exist or there is some other error while loading, ccwl crashes brutally with a backtrace. We need to capture and report this cleanly. Any errors in recursively loaded files must also be captured and reported cleanly.\n\n`load` is a built-in and we don't have much control over it. Creating `ccwl-workflow`—a wrapper around `load`—could be the way to go.","files":null}]}